; Issue #993: --related drops generated postings from null-post multi-commodity expansion
;
; When a transaction has a null posting (no amount) that must balance across
; multiple commodities, ledger expands it: the first commodity (alphabetically)
; goes directly into the null post, while subsequent commodities get new
; ITEM_GENERATED|POST_CALCULATED postings on the same account.
;
; Previously, --related would skip those generated postings, producing
; incomplete output whose content depended on commodity sort order.

2013/10/05 * Shopping
    Expenses:Food          5 A
    Assets:Cash          -20 B
    Income:Currency

; Without --related the balance shows both A and B in Income:Currency
test bal
               -20 B  Assets:Cash
                 5 A  Expenses:Food
                -5 A
                20 B  Income:Currency
--------------------
                   0
end test

; With --related cash, Income:Currency should show both -5 A and 20 B,
; not just -5 A (the non-generated posting).
test bal --related cash
                 5 A  Expenses:Food
                -5 A
                20 B  Income:Currency
--------------------
                20 B
end test
